# Cloudflare Pages redirects (`migrate-deploy-to-cloudflare-pages`
# spec: bare `301` is canonical; `301!` is Netlify-only).
#
# USMR Phase 5.5.16-pt157 — destinations match `trailingSlash:
# "never"` from astro.config.ts. Pre-pt157 redirects pointed at
# `/faq/` and `/writing/` (with trailing slashes) — but those URLs
# themselves 301-redirect to the no-trailing-slash form, so legacy
# inbound links followed a TWO-HOP redirect chain (e.g.
# /faqs → /faq/ → /faq), wasting crawl budget AND adding
# user-perceptible latency on cold-cache requests.
/faqs    /faq                   301
# /bridge → /platform#bridge redirect dropped in USMR Phase 5.2.8;
# /bridge now resolves to a real page. The /platform <section id=
# "bridge"> anchor from 5.1q.4 stays in place for legacy inbound
# links that hit /platform#bridge directly.

# Header nav surfaces the writing index as "Blog" — both URLs land on
# the same canonical content. Added in USMR Phase 5.5.
/blog          /writing              301
/blog/         /writing              301
/blog/*        /writing/:splat       301
